ZH: 他对这个问题不闻不问。
EN: He doesn't care about this issue at all.
ZH: 她总是不闻不问，让人觉得很冷淡。
EN: She always behaves indifferently, making people feel detached.
ZH: 老板对员工的工作进展不闻不问，导致公司出了很多问题。
EN: The boss's lack of concern about the progress of the employees' work has caused many problems in the company.
ZH: 我们必须向他询问，不能不闻不问。
EN: We must ask him, we can't just ignore it.
ZH: 如果你不闻不问，你就无法了解事情的真相。
EN: If you turn a blind eye, you won't be able to know the truth.
ZH: 我对他的私事不感兴趣，所以一直不闻不问。
EN: I'm not interested in his personal affairs, so I've been ignoring them.
ZH: 这是一个非常严重的问题，我们不能不闻不问。
EN: This is a very serious problem, we cannot ignore it.
ZH: 我们必须对此加以关注，不能一直不闻不问。
EN: We must pay attention to this, we can't just keep turning a blind eye.
ZH: 如果你不闻不问，就无法理解别人的处境。
EN: If you ignore it, you won't be able to understand others' situations.
ZH: 他对身边的事情从来不闻不问。
EN: He never turns a blind eye to things happening around him.
ZH: 在工作中，你不能不闻不问，需要积极参与。
EN: In work, you cannot ignore it, you need to actively participate.
ZH: 我们需要向他们询问，而不能不闻不问。
EN: We need to ask them, we can't just turn a blind eye.
ZH: 老师总是不闻不问学生的学习状况。
EN: The teacher always ignores the students' learning progress.
ZH: 大家都在议论这个事情，只有你不闻不问。
EN: Everyone is talking about this issue, only you are turning a blind eye.
ZH: 我们需要对这个问题表示关注，不能不闻不问。
EN: We need to show concern about this issue, we can't just ignore it.
ZH: 她常常不闻不问自己的家人，导致之间感情疏远。
EN: She often ignores her own family, leading to a distant relationship.
ZH: 如果你对待事情不闻不问，别人就会觉得你漠不关心。
EN: If you treat things indifferently, others will feel that you are indifferent.
ZH: 他从不关心政治，对于这方面的事情总是不闻不问。
EN: He never cares about politics and always turns a blind eye to it.
